# COMPASS Project — Complete Summary

## What COMPASS Is

COMPASS is a student career exploration platform — a full-stack Next.js web application that helps
high school students reflect on their interests, activities, and goals through structured reflection
sessions every 3 weeks. Counselors can view student profiles and signals. An AI layer (Claude +
Voyage AI) synthesizes student data into "signal profiles" with interest clusters, character
signals, trajectory shifts, and a compressed summary. A pgvector-powered map surfaces personalized
career/major recommendations.

---

## Architecture

Monorepo (Turborepo + pnpm workspaces):
```
compass/
├── apps/web/          — Next.js 14 App Router (student + counselor + admin UI)
├── apps/ai-service/   — FastAPI Python (AI endpoints: synthesis, embeddings, prompts)
├── apps/mobile/       — React Native (untouched)
├── packages/db/       — Prisma ORM + schema + Supabase WASM client
├── packages/ui/       — Shared UI components
├── packages/types/    — Shared TypeScript types
├── packages/config/   — Shared tsconfig/eslint
├── turbo.json         — Turborepo task config
└── CONTRIBUTING.md    — Migration workflow docs
```

**Tech stack:** Next.js 14, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Prisma 6 (WASM), Supabase (PostgreSQL +
pgvector), Clerk (auth — student/counselor/admin roles), Upstash Redis (caching) + QStash
(background jobs), Anthropic claude-sonnet-4-6 (synthesis), Voyage AI (1024-dim embeddings),
Vercel (web hosting), Railway (AI service hosting).

